<%# 2026-05-18 — `BundlesController#create` Turbo Stream response.

    Three streams composed:

      1. Append the new bundle's tile to the `/games` bundles shelf
         row (`.bundles-shelf-row`). The selector targets the inner
         row's class because `ShelfComponent` doesn't stamp a DOM id
         on the row — the `bundles-shelf-row` class is unique on the
         page (only the bundles outer shelf carries it). Uses the
         `targets` attribute (Turbo's selector form) rather than
         `target` (id form) so we can match on the class selector.

      2. Replace the bundles modal partial. The re-rendered partial
         carries `bundle: @bundle` as a local so the title text,
         inline-edit PATCH URL, and inner Turbo Frame `src` are pre-
         populated server-side AND the dialog mounts the
         `bundles-modal-autoopen` Stimulus controller, which calls
         `showModal()` on `connect()`. The result: the modal opens
         directly inside the freshly-created bundle without an extra
         user click.

      3. Append the flash notice to the toast container. The toast
         container always renders unconditionally in the layout
         (`shared/_flash_toasts`), so an `append` is safe even when no
         flash has fired this page-life. The toast Stimulus controller
         (mounted via `data-controller="toast"`) self-dismisses the
         toast after the default delay.
%>
<turbo-stream action="append" targets=".bundles-shelf-row">
  <template>
    <%= render(Games::BundleTileComponent.new(bundle: @bundle)) %>
  </template>
</turbo-stream>

<%= turbo_stream.replace "bundles-modal" do %>
  <%= render "games/bundles_modal", bundle: @bundle %>
<% end %>

<turbo-stream action="append" targets=".toast-container">
  <template>
    <div class="toast toast-notice" data-controller="toast" role="status">
      <%= t("bundles.flash.created") %>
    </div>
  </template>
</turbo-stream>
